SIMPLE: hocus
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hocus
<hw>Ho"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hocus-pocus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deceive or cheat.</def>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To adulterate; to drug; <as>as, liquor is said to be
<ex>hocused</ex> for the purpose of stupefying the drinker</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To stupefy with drugged liquor.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hocus</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hocus
<hw>Ho"cus</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who cheats or
deceives.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Drugged liquor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hocus-pocus</ent>⟦br⟧
